title: punjabi lok nach academy - first place @ bhangra in the 6ix 2017
tags: Gabroo Tv;Gabroo;Giddha Tv;GTV;GTV Bhangra;Harjot Hundal;Punjab;Punjabi;Virsa;Dhol;Tumbi;Punjabi Folk Nach Academy;Bhangra in the six;Bhangra in the 6ix;Jolly Bawa;Live Bhangra;Toronto Bhangra Competition
description:
This video is special. I had goosebumps watching this live. I had goosebumps while editing this, and though a video will never do this set justice, I know you too will experience goosebumps while watching this performance.

This is as Folk as it gets, the entire set from start to finish is an absolute work of art, especially the Jhoomar segment. The singers voice is music to my ears, the boliyan are perfect, and Ustad Jolly Bawa Ji on the dhol is an absolute beast. It is my absolute honor and pleasure to introduce to you, the Punjabi Lok Nach Academy with their First Place performance at Bhangra in the 6ix 2017.

--

title: first class bhangra @ motor city bhangra 2016
tags: Gabroo Tv;Gabroo;Giddha Tv;GTV;GTV Bhangra;Harjot Hundal;Punjab;Punjabi;Virsa;Dhol;Tumbi;First Class Bhangra;Motor City Bhangra;Live Bhangra;Folk Bhangra;Traditional Bhangra;FCB Bhangr
description:
On February 28 2015, First Class Bhangra was performing at a show in Washington DC, when their music abruptly shut off, in lieu of a technical error. Instead of stopping their performance, they continued, and danced live to their Dholi (watch the link below at the 3 minute mark.) Nearly a year later, the lads from First Class Bhangra are back to perform Live Bhangra the proper way, at Motor City Bhangra 2016, with a full band. This is a story of their journey on the weekend of this performance!

Performance in 2015 when their music shut off:
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=179JFCVUVjs

--

Participants:

Red Pagh: Sid Pandit & Ram Mahalingam
Ferozi Pagh: Shubhit Singh & Mitra Patel
Blue Pagh: Ravi Mehta & Jigar Saraiya
Yellow Pagh: Umer Qureshi & Akash Bansal
Dholi: Tejasvir Singh Rekhi
Vocalist: Ikamjit Singh Gill
Secondary Vocalist: Rajvir Singh Kahlon
Chimta: Rohan Bansal
Dhad: Kavin Sanghavi
Harmonium: Sehaj Singh Rekhi

--

Special thanks:

Rupa Mehta: Setting up secondary microphones, and recording slow motion footage
Hardik Singh, Ian Asenjo, Kavin Sanghavi: Setting up the GoPro onstage cameras.
Krupa Patel: Being extremely helpful and accommodating during the weekend/filming process of this show.
Gary Khehra: Providing the platform (Motor City Bhangra 2016) to film this video.
Akshdeep Dhaliwal, Dhir Patwa, Disha Sharma, Nikita Patkar, Nithin Santhanam, Rajesh Ravikumar, Shivani Brahmbhatt, Ankur Toshniwal, Jay Vakil, Jayveer Sodiwal, for your support during the weekend of this show.
Minesh Patel: Taking the cover photo for this video.

--

First Class Bhangra links:

http://www.firstclassbhangra.com
http://www.facebook.com/FirstClassBhangra
http://www.instagram.com/firstclassbhangra
http://twitter.com/fcbhangra

--

Background song:

Indian Summer, performed by Jai Wolf.
Care of Believe Music, [Merlin] InertiaPtyLtd, SME, and INgrooves

--

title: shaan punjab dee @ bhangra arena 2019
tags: Gabroo Tv;Gabroo;Giddha Tv;GTV;GTV Bhangra;Harjot Hundal;Punjab;Punjabi;Virsa;Dhol;Tumbi;Shaan Punjab Dee;SPD Bhangra;Bhangra Arena;Bhangra Arena 2019
description:
This is Shaan Punjab Dee, performing at Bhangra Arena 2019. Shaan Punjab Dee is from Toronto Canada, and they traveled all the way to New Delhi, India, to compete at this competition.

--

Dancers:
Red: Prabh Saini & Jagmeet Saini
Blue: Inderpreet Dhaliwal & Jashanpreet Dhaliwal
Green: Karan Bains & Navdip Sidhu
Yellow: Goondeep Cambow & Harnaz Singh

Band Members:
Dholi: Ustaad Nasib Singh
Singer: Honey sidhu
Bugchu: Professor Harnam Singh Sandhu
Sarangi: Sarbjit Singh 
Tumba/flute: Honey Dhillon
Tumbi: Kirat
Algozey: Avtar Singh 
Chimta: Pawandeep Singh

--

I'd like to apologize, to my viewers, for the poor audio quality. There were technical issues that I experienced with the sound technician, sadly I was not able to capture this band's performance in full glory. I am hopeful that the Bhangra Arena committee and I can work to avoid technical difficulties like this in the future.

Here are a few words provided by Shaan Punjab Dee, regarding their performance:

We received a standing ovation and also opened many debates. Some statements were made during a speech by a Judge regarding their performance that triggered the audience and the team itself but it only took place because of the lack of communication between the organizers and the judges. Shaan Punjab Dee seeks to gain more experience to form the best live performance that suits India as well as countries outside of India. At the end, everyone ended up with some things to learn. Future is expected to be BRIGHTER.

--

title: shaan punjab dee - first place @ big 10 bhangra 2017
tags: Gabroo Tv;Gabroo;Giddha Tv;GTV;GTV Bhangra;Harjot Hundal;Punjab;Punjabi;Virsa;Dhol;Tumbi;Shaan Punjab Dee;Big 10 Bhangra;Big Ten Bhangra;Best Bhangra;Empire Bhangra;Bhangra Empire
description:
This is the video you've all been waiting for. Wait no more :) What I find amazing is that Shaan Punjab Dee performed a few weeks prior to this performance, at Bhangra Fever 7, with a routine that was roughly 60% different. For them to change soo much, and execute it soo well, is an amazing display of the talent on this team. I present to you, Shaan Punjab Dee's First Place performance at Big 10 Bhangra 2017.

SPECIAL SHOUTOUT: Gurjeet Singh Pabla (GSP) the DJ who made the mix that Shaan Punjab Dee performed to. SPD had originally chosen a different set of DJ's to make their mix. Due to a misunderstanding, those DJ's leaked SPD's routine, in an effort to inflict harm. Ya'll just harmed yourself, because the spotlight could have been focused on you. Let this be a lesson to uphold respect and dignity in every situation. Gurjeet Pabla, big ups bruv! Bhangra teams, need a mix? Hit up GSP - HH

--

title: duniya de rang @ big 10 bhangra 2017
tags: Gabroo Tv;Gabroo;Giddha Tv;GTV;GTV Bhangra;Harjot Hundal;Punjab;Punjabi;Virsa;Dhol;Tumbi;Big 10 Bhangra;Big Ten Bhangra;Duniya De Rang;DDR Bhangra;American Bhangra
description:
PREFACE: PLEASE LEAVE SOME LOVE FOR DUNIYA DE RANG IN THE COMMENTS BELOW!

This video is special. This performance is special. Duniya De Rang is a newly formed Bhangra team, a special collaboration of entirely non-desi bhangra dancers within the Bhangra Circuit. In the society that we live in today, with negativity stemming left and right, this is such a beautiful beautiful thing to see, dancers from different backgrounds and ethnicities, coming together to celebrate our culture with us.

DDR hails from well known Bhangra teams such as Alamo City Bhangra, Anakh-E-Gabroo, Cal Bhangra, Cornell Bhangra, Da Real Punjabiz, Rochester Bhangra, and Virginia-Tech Bhangra. This performance was put together to demonstrate the love and passion each and ever dancer has for Bhangra and to thank the Bhangra circuit for introducing them to this art form. That being said, I hope you enjoy Duniya De Rang's performance at Big 10 Bhangra 2017.

--

title: khirre phul gulab de @ bruin bhangra 2016
tags: Gabroo Tv;Gabroo;Giddha Tv;GTV;GTV Bhangra;Harjot Hundal;Punjab;Punjabi;Virsa;Dhol;Tumbi;Khirre Phul Gulab De;Bruin Bhangra;Bruin Bhangra 2016;KPGB Bhangra;Los Angeles Bhangra Competition
description:
Khirre Phul Gulab De came to perform at Bruin Bhangra 2016 for many reasons, but they had even more reasons not to attend this competition. In the past few months, the members of this team have dealt with many, many setbacks, but none so prominent as the loss of their teammate, dholi, DJ, and brother, Anooj Kumar Trivedi. 

Anooj was a member of KPGD when it first began in 2010, and had danced with many of the team members on Gajjde Gabroo and Gajjdi Jawani before that. His talents extended far from simply being an amazing dancer, dholi, and music production artist, as he was a genuinely kind-hearted soul who was always the source of entertainment and positive energy to all those around him. 

Khirre Phul Gulab De dedicates this performance in his memory, to a flower who didn't get the chance to fully bloom, to the person who reminds them how short and precious life is, and that we can and will push through anything and everything, for it is a privilege to be here. 

The tribute to Anooj Trivedi done at the end of this routine was not officially part of the routine, and KPGD asked not to be judged on it. His presence was felt with us that night and forever will each time we step onto stage. 

--

description:
Some people have verbalized opinions that I favor this team, when I write their video descriptions. If you ask me, I just say it like it is. Watch the first minute of this video, and you'll immediately see the immense amount of hard work and dedication this clan has invested into this performance. Did they make a few mistakes? Sure. Did some of their gimmicks fail? Absolutely. But they pushed the bar further (as always) and all you see on their faces are beautiful beautiful smiles as they pound the dust off that stage. Don't take my word for it, watch this video, I promise it'll be the best 9 minutes you invested into something today.

For those of you that disliked this description, life is beautiful, but short. Focus that energy into something positive. I still love y'all. Now watch my First Class family with their second place performance at Bruin Bhangra 2016.

--

title: da real punjabiz @ bruin bhangra 2016
description:
I have seen this team put in an immense amount of hard work at every show I've had to pleasure to attend with them, but they never seemed to get the recognition that I felt they deserved. I've been down the same road, on a Bhangra team that took years to finally place first, but when it finally happened, it was such a rewarding feeling. That's how I feel about this performance. Seeing this team grow over the past few years, I felt a personal sense of pride seeing them place first. This performance is clean. It is raw. It is simple, yet elegant. They mixed up such a great selection of music, and the choreo is absolutely on point, and it is a very well deserved First place performance.

I am happy to introduce to you, the First place team at Bruin Bhangra 2016 (the Super Bowl of Bhangra) Da Real Punjabiz.

--

title: tune squad @ bruin bhangra 2016
tags: Gabroo Tv;Gabroo;Giddha Tv;GTV;GTV Bhangra;Harjot Hundal;Punjab;Punjabi;Virsa;Dhol;Tumbi;Tune Squad;Bruin Bhangra;Tune Squad Bhangra
description:
This performance started off with quite the intro, with a tribute to all of the competitive performing teams at Bruin Bhangra this year. For those of you who don't know, Tune Squad is a group that's comprised of many veteran dancers from the Bhangra circuit. Some of these dancers have danced on teams such as Anakh E Gabroo, VCU Bhangra, and Cornell Bhangra, just to name a few. Collectively, they have massive Bhangra experience, and it definitely shows in this unique and entertaining performance.

The future of the Tune Squad is not certain, as this set was a one time set made by friends who used to compete against each other at Bhangra competitions. They've now found themselves dancing together as one unit on the same stage. If that doesn't show you the power of music and Bhangra, then I don't know what will. Well done, gentlemen. I present to you, the Tune Squad Bhangra group at Bruin Bhangra 2016.
--

P.S. Put on your headphones and crank up the volume, your ears will thank you ;)

description:
Shaan Punjab Dee takes their 6th first place trophy in a row at Bruin Bhangra's 20th Anniversary, which took place in Downtown Los Angeles on May 27, 2018. SPD is a bhangra team of elite dancers situated in the heart of Brampton, Canada. 

Shaan Punjab Dee is the first team ever from Brampton, Ontario to be placed first in the last 20 years of Bruin Bhangra Competition. 

We hope this team continues to attract the youth so they can utilize their time and energy towards living a healthy lifestyle and stay folk. Congratulations, Shaan Punjab Dee.

title: duniya de rang @ bruin bhangra's 20th anniversary - bruin bhangra xx (2018)
tags: Gabroo Tv;Gabroo;Giddha Tv;GTV;GTV Bhangra;Harjot Hundal;Punjab;Punjabi;Virsa;Dhol;Tumbi;DDR Bhangra;Bruin XX;Bruin Bhangra;Bruin Bhangra 2018;DTLA Bhangra Competition;American Bhangra;Non Indian Bhangra;Duniya De Rang
description:
This is Duniya De Rang, with their beautiful performance at Bruin Bhangra XX.

For the non-Desi dancers of Duniya De Rang, Bhangra was not an inheritance, but a gift from their mentors.

-Mentors who taught them Punjabi traditions.
-Mentors who fostered friendships.
-Mentors who became family.

To give thanks, the team invited 16 of their mentors and friends from across the United States to join them on stage. The team spent weeks practicing hundreds of miles apart, and could only afford 1 full team practice the night before Bruin. 

Despite all odds, these 32 dancers hope their performance will help you, the viewer, remember the loved ones who brought Bhangra into your own life. 

Finally, the piano piece used, Merry Christmas Mr. Lawrence, is special. It was the last instrumental duet Angela and her best friend performed before his passing, and then became the first piece she ever choreographed. This time, Angela would like to dedicate this piece to her teammates-- to thank them for their time and trust, and to never forget the love they felt together on stage.

Facebook: www.facebook.com/ddrbhangra
Instagram: @ddrbhangra

--

title: duniya de rang - first place @ buckeye mela 2018
tags: Gabroo Tv;Gabroo;Giddha Tv;GTV;GTV Bhangra;Harjot Hundal;Punjab;Punjabi;Virsa;Dhol;Tumbi;Duniya De Rang;DDR Bhangra;American Bhangra;Gora Bhangra;Buckeye Bhangra;Buckeye Mela
description:
Duniya De Rang (DDR) is a national collaboration of experienced non-Desi dancers. DDR is built on two principles-- 1) to celebrate their passion for Bhangra, and 2) to express their gratitude for everything the Bhangra community has taught them about Punjabi culture.

Because these friends hail from across the country, DDR is never able to have a full team practice until competition weekend. As such, they view competitions as a rare privilege to experience the joy of dancing together; they hope that you, the viewer, can share in their happiness through this performance.

title: pitt nrityamala @ bhangra in the burgh 8 (2014)
description:
Performing in their hometown of Pittsburgh Pennsylvania, this is Pitt Nrityamala performing at Bhangra In The Burgh 8 (2014).

Nrityamala is the University of Pittsburgh's premier Indian classical dance team. It was started in 2006 and has been expanding ever since. They are the only collegiate classical dance team in the Pittsburgh area and strive to not only keep in touch with their classical dance backgrounds, but also to promote the art by performing on campus and across the East Coast. Their team consists of passionate dancers trained in various dance forms, including Bharatanatyam, Kuchipudi, Odissi, and Kathak. As a team, they are traditional in their style and fuse the different forms together in order to create a unique dance presentation.

title: ministry of bhangra chicago @ bhangra in the burgh 2016
tags: Gabroo Tv;Gabroo;Giddha Tv;GTV;GTV Bhangra;Harjot Hundal;Punjab;Punjabi;Virsa;Dhol;Tumbi;Bhangra In The Burgh;Ministry of Bhangra Chicago;Chicago Bhangra Team
description:
I've seen many performances from the Windy City MOB. This is, hands down, their best performance to date! Their mix is sick, their outfits are sick (though I do miss the ties) and the energy level/choreo is on point. To my MOB fam, keep up the great work, looking forward to seeing what y'all bring to Bruin this year. Until then, I hope you all enjoy their performance at Bhangra at the Burgh 2016. 

I would also like to send a big shoutout to Viknesh Lakshmanan. I experienced a sudden death of an immediate family member a few days before this competition, and I had to cancel my trip to Bhangra in the Burgh 2016. I mailed my camera equipment to Pittsburgh, and Viknesh stepped up to the plate to record all of the team performances. Thank you, Vik!

--

title: bhangra all stars sydney - second place @ bhangra fever 2019
description:
These lads, again, embarked on a long journey from Sydney Australia to Buffalo New York, for Bhangra Fever 2019. One thing is clear, the judges had a tough task on their hands, because this performance is beautiful in every regard. I know you will enjoy this one, I present to you my family from across the pond - BASS, with their second place performance at Bhangra Fever 2019.

Though I was not able to attend Bhangra Fever 2019 (I was at another competition taking place on the same day, Bhangra Blowout) the Bhangra Fever team and I worked hard to secure a good videographer to record the show. Regrettably, the person whom we chose to work with did not meet our expectations. All being said, I would like to send my apologies to all of the teams at Bhangra Fever this year, as this video is not up to the normal GTV standards.

--

title: the michigan bhangra team @ bhangra fever 7 (2017)
tags: Gabroo Tv;Gabroo;Giddha Tv;GTV;GTV Bhangra;Harjot Hundal;Punjab;Punjabi;Virsa;Dhol;Tumbi;Bhangra Fever 7;The Michigan Bhangra Team;Michigan Bhangra
description:
Back with a vengeance! This The Michigan Bhangra Team, with a fresh new set of dancers, performing for their first time @ Bhangra Fever 7!

The Michigan Bhangra Team (MBT) was started in the Fall of 2000 with a very distinct vision: to promote awareness of Punjabi culture and the importance of diversity and multiculturalism. We accomplish these goals by performing at numerous charity and cultural events for both our campus community and the community at large. Our team is known for our energy on and off stage; we are driven to inspire others with our passion, dedication, and unique style. Our performance is based upon a foundation of camaraderie, creativity, and spirit, all elements we hope will work to transcend social boundaries to build a sense of community and awareness.

--

description:

Members were placed all around the hall and threw multi-colored glow sticks (unexpectedly) at an insanely synchronized interval. The adrenaline of the audience instantly jumped to 100. title: first class bhangra @ elite 8 bhangra 2015
tags: Gabroo;Giddha;GTV;Harjot Hundal;Bhangra;Punjab;Punjabi;Virsa;Dhol;Tumbi;First Class Bhangra;FCB Bhangra;Pittsburgh (City/Town/Village);Elite 8 Bhangra;Elite 8 Bhangra Invitational;Bhangra Competition;2015;Bhangra (Musical Genre);Gabroo Tv;GTV Bhangra
description:
It is said that elite moments happen at Elite 8 Bhangra Invitational. This performance definitely classifies that. The true strength of a team is determined when real world tests are presented in real world scenarios at the most of unexpected times. When this teams music abruptly turned off approximately 2 minutes into the performance (due to a technical mishap) they were presented a variety of choices. 

They could have stopped dancing, or they could have embraced that this was meant to be and continue dancing. They continued dancing. When you push forward, your side supporters push forward, the crowd pushes forward, and your new one drum stereo pushes forward. This, is what separates the boys from the men. This, is what makes you a winner. This, is an elite moment. Landing on stage via First Class Air flight E8BI15, this is First Class Bhangra with the most memorable performance of the night, perhaps even the 2015 Bhangra year.

--

Elite 8 Bhangra Invitational 2015 took place in Washington DC (USA) on February 28 2015, at the George Washington Universities Lisner Auditorium. For more information about the show, please visit www.elite8bhangra.com

--

title: shaan punjab di @ warrior bhangra 2014
description:
This is Shaan Punjab Di, an all girls live Bhangra team representing Northern California, USA, performing at Warrior Bhangra 2014. Shaan Punjab Di takes pride in currently being the only all-girls live bhangra team from the United States, their passion for dancing and love for our culture is what has motivated them to go against the odds and compete in live bhangra where there are mainly teams formed by all males.

Warrior Bhangra 2014 was held at the Bob Hope Auditorium in Stockton California on March 29 2014.

title: bhangra empire @ warrior bhangra 2014
tags: Gabroo;Giddha;GTV;Bhangra;Punjab;Punjabi;Virsa;Dhol;Tumbi;Bhangra Empire;Warrior Bhangra Competition 2014;Warrior Bhangra 2014;Bhangra Competition 2014;Harjot Hundal;GTV Bhangra
description:
Representing California's Bay Area, this is Bhangra Empire performing performing at Warrior Bhangra 2014. Established in 2006, Bhangra Empire is proud to share its roots with the Bay Area community, while showcasing its talent worldwide as one of North Americas premiere dance teams. From the White House to Americas Got Talent, from the Golden State Warriors NBA court to the World Series Champion SF Giants MLB stadium, from an overseas performance at the HMV Hammersmith Apollo in London with 5,000 viewers to an overseas performance at the Formula One Grand Prix in Bahrain  Bhangra Empire strives to set a new standard in entertainment, bring Punjabi culture to the mainstream, and take Bhangra to every corner of the world.

Warrior Bhangra 2014 was held at the Bob Hope Auditorium in Stockton California on March 29 2014.

description:
This is Australia's all female Bhangra team, Haneri Punjab Di, performing at Bhangra Down Under 2015. Haneri Punjab Di (HPD) is Sydney's preeminent, all girls, Bhangra team. Bringing a fusion of folk and contemporary Bhangra to the forefront, Haneri Punjab Di dances straight from their heart!

title: ministry of bhangra sydney @ bhangra down under 2015
tags: Gabroo Tv;Gabroo;Giddha Tv;GTV;GTV Bhangra;Harjot Hundal;Punjab;Punjabi;Virsa;Dhol;Tumbi;Ministry of Bhangra;Sydney (City/Town/Village);Australia (Country);Bhangra Down Under 2015;BDU 2015;MOB Sydney;Australia Bhangra;Bhangra (Musical Genre)
description:
After their killer First place performance at Harbor City Bhangra (which also took place in Australia earlier this year) the boys from Sydney Australia turned up the heat a notch and came back even stronger! Formed in 2010, but exponentially stronger in 2015; I'm glad to have gotten to know them the past few years, as their love and passion for Bhangra in Australia is unmatched. 

Though I had made a statement previously, in regards to my opinion of which team should have placed first, it is also important to note that my brothers from Sydney did an amazing job. Performing with 16 people on one stage is no easy feat, you guys did it well. My favorite part was the entire "Guddi Wangu' segment. The choreo, the movement, the gimmick, well done. I have seen soo much improvement from you guys, you guys are most definitely one of the 'top tier' teams in Australia, and I cannot wait to see you again in the near future!

Performing with an army of 16 strong, this is the Ministry of Bhangra, representing Sydney Australia, performing at Bhangra Down Under 2015. The mix is absolute fire, one that you'll be sure to enjoy!

tags: Gabroo Tv;Gabroo;Giddha Tv;GTV;GTV Bhangra;Harjot Hundal;Punjab;Punjabi;Virsa;Dhol;Tumbi;Bhangra Down Under;BDU2015;BDU15;Australia (Country);Melbourne (City/Town/Village);Melbourne Bhangra Regiment;Australia Bhangra;Australia Punjabi Culture
description:
The Third place winner for two consecutive years, this is Melbourne's very own 'Melbourne Bhangra Regiment' performing at Bhangra Down Under 2015. This was their second run of the night, as their first performance abruptly ended in lieu of a technical mishap.

Established in 2012, this team started out with 2 boys dancing at various weddings and parties. Now they have become the largest team in Melbourne and just pulled off the biggest coed performance in Australian Bhangra Histroy at this years BDU going in with a team of 16!

I received the pleasure of meeting this team at last years show, and it's refreshing to see how much they have improved across the board, in respect to choreo, energy, execution, and expressions. The new outfits are aesthetically pleasing as well. To MBR, keep up the good work - hh.

--

title: l fresh the lion (live performance) @ bhangra down under 2014
description:
L-FRESH The LION is renowned for his powerful presence, inspiring live shows & for having some of the most intelligent lyrics in Australian Hip Hop. His debut album One (released in May along with a national headline tour) received stellar reviews. Since 2009, he has toured nationally with Hip Hop legends Nas, Chali 2na (Jurassic 5), DJ Qbert, MC Supernatural, Talib Kweli and Dead Prez. Locally, he has shared stages with Horrorshow, The Herd, Hermitude, Urthboy and many more.

Following the release of One, L-FRESH The LION toured nationally across Australia; touching down in Sydney, Melbourne, Brisbane, Perth and Adelaide; taking his 7-member band with him. 

His latest single 'Survive (feat. MK-1)' was recently selected by MTV Iggy for their Best New Hip Hop playlist.

His sound is uplifting and universally accessible, inspired by the conscious, soulful Hip Hop movement in the U.S. in the late 1990s and early 2000s. Combine that with his love and respect for his cultural and ancestral roots of the Sikhs from Panjab, India, and you have an individual like no other in the music scene.

In understanding the social responsibility bestowed on him by the legacy of Hip Hop culture and his cultural ancestors, L-FRESH The LION has tirelessly dedicated himself to working in the community. In particular, he has aligned himself with many social justice issues.

He has appeared on Channel 10s The Project, ABC Radio National and ABC Local Radio for his work in community and has spoken at a variety of events and conferences such as TEDxParramatta and for Amnesty International.

At present, he is an ambassador for All Together Now, Australias only national charity that exists solely to address racism.

He is also the founder of the Power To The Peaceful Community, a clothing label and online community that exists to encourage everlasting and meaningful dialogue around peace and peaceful relationships.

--

title: bhangra rulez @ bhangra down under 2018
tags: Gabroo Tv;Gabroo;Giddha Tv;GTV;GTV Bhangra;Harjot Hundal;Punjab;Punjabi;Virsa;Dhol;Tumbi;BDU2018;Bhangra Down Under;Australia Bhangra Team;Perth Bhangra;Bhangra Rules;Bhangra Rulez
description:
Being from North America, I always find it refreshing to travel abroad to see fresh new choreo from teams overseas. This team, Bhangra Rulez, is from Perth Australia. I must say, their choreo was simple, in the best way possible, but it has a very strong FOLK flair to it, and those who know me, know I love folk. 

It's safe to say, they made a fan out of me. All being said, this is Bhangra Rulez performing at Bhangra Down Under 2018.

Bhangra Down Under took place at Bunjil Place, in Narre Warren Australia, on October 6 2018. For more information regarding Bhangra Down Under, be sure to visit them on Facebook or Insta.

title: marakh punjab dhi @ solano bhangra 2013
description:
Solano Bhangra 2013 took place in Vacaville California on September 21 2013. This show is based entirely from the local communities support. Many parents in the community take part in organizing this show. This includes along Ustad Manjinder Singh Dhaliwal, and other members of the Gabroo Punjabis, who help organize and teach Bhangra to the students. Solano Bhangra is a "summer camp" if you will, that teaches the students all about Bhangra, sportsmanship, discipline, and camaraderie. At the end of the Bhangra camp, this show is organized for the students to show the community, their parents, their peers, what they've learned over the summer. Some of these students have spent time on a stage before, and for some of these students it is their first time.

This is Marakh Punjab Dhi, a Giddha team consisting of the mothers from Solano County!
